cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this library in research or training pipeline development, please cite it as below."
type: dataset
title: "Bio Constitution Rules Library"
abstract: >
  30 machine-readable constitutional rules for biological dual-use content
  classification across six domains (virology, toxicology, synthetic biology,
  genomics, pathogen biology, dual-use chemistry). Each rule includes biological
  reasoning, edge cases with resolutions, a four-tier severity system, and
  explicit regulatory mapping to NSABB DURC, FSAP, BWC/CWC, Australia Group,
  and WHO Laboratory Biosafety Manual frameworks. Accompanied by a 1,063-record
  synthetic training corpus and end-to-end Constitutional Classifier evaluation
  achieving 100% accuracy on a 42-query pilot (+47.6pp over generic CBRN
  baseline) and 86.7% on 5-fold cross-validation (+26pp).
authors:
